# AI Misinformation Detection System - Tasks

## 1. Project Initialization
- [ ] Initialize `backend` directory and set up Python environment
- [ ] Create `frontend` React app using Vite (`npx create-vite@latest frontend --template react`)
- [ ] Install Tailwind CSS in `frontend`

## 2. Backend Implementation (FastAPI)
- [ ] Set up `backend/main.py` and CORS middleware
- [ ] Create `backend/api/routes.py` with endpoints `/verify_article` and `/verify_claim`
- [ ] Implement `backend/llm/` module for Ollama (`qwen2.5:7b`) integration
- [ ] Implement `backend/retrieval/` module to handle FAISS vector DB and `bge-small-en` embeddings
- [ ] Implement `backend/pipeline/` logic for sentence segmentation, claim filtering, retrieval, and reasoning
- [ ] Handle persistent storage in `backend/storage/` (index.faiss & metadata)

## 3. Frontend Implementation (React & Tailwind)
- [ ] Clean up default Vite boilerplate and configure layout
- [ ] Build Application UI (Input textarea for raw article, Submission button)
- [ ] Implement API client to communicate with FastAPI backend
- [ ] Build Real-time Results Panel with dynamic verdict badges (Supported, Refuted, Unverifiable)
- [ ] Display extracted claims, verdict, reasoning, and evidence sources

## 4. End-to-End Integration
- [ ] Test the full pipeline with sample articles containing factual claims
- [ ] Verify error handling and UI loading states
